rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
Primary Entity representing all athletes. These include professional, minor league, and amateur athletes.
People who are athletes:
## Athletes on a team (e.g. Yao Ming, Footballer David Silva).
## Athletes who compete alone (e.g. professional snowboarder and skateboarder Shaun White, logroller J. R. Salzman, and ice skater Viktor Petrenko).
## Amateur Olympic athletes (e.g. olympic rower Jamie Schroeder, curler Anette Norberg). Use the more specific subtype mso:olympics.athlete in these cases.
## Amateur athletes with no Olympic experience (e.g. roller derby skater Joan Weston).
## University athletes (e.g. Maya Moore of the UConn Huskies, Akbar Ansari of the Cambridge University Cricket Club).
## People involved in sports that require the use of machinery, such as motor-sports (e.g.: Danica Patrick, Dale Earnhardt, Mark Webber).
## People with athletic hobbies (e.g. President Obama, who plays basketball occasionally).
## People involved in entertainment based on sporting events (e.g. Harlem Globetrotter George Bell).
## People involved in athletic competitions (e.g. champion logroller J.R. Salzman, caber tosser Bill Anderson).
Things that are NOT athletes:
## Animals (e.g. Seabiscuit).
## Teams (e.g. Manchester United Football Club). Use mso:sports.team in these cases.
## People not participating in a sport (e.g. competitive eater Takeru Kobayashi).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Athlete

For example, the Japanese Grand Prix occurred at the Suzuka Circuit from 1987 to 2006. However, the Super Bowl occurs at a different location every year.

rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. If one needs to specify a facility for a recurring sporting event, the property sports.recurring_sporting_event.facility should be created. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.recurring_sporting_event_facility relationship to the mso:sports.facility that the recurring event occurs in.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Facility
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.recurring_sporting_event_facility relationship to the mso:sports.recurring_sporting_event that occurs regularly at the facility. Note that not all mso:sports.recurring_sporting_events occur at the same place every occurrence. This relationship should be used only when the instances of the mso:sports.recurring_sporting_event occur regularly at the same facility. Otherwise, use mso:time.event.location on the individual events if the instances occur at difference locations as a matter of course.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A sports competition that involves roping, wrestling, and riding horses and cattle.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rodeo

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing sports teams that represent an educational institution, e.g. high school and college football teams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: School Sports Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a school sports team to the brand of the team. For example, the University of Michigan Football Team is a part of the "Michigan Wolverines" athletics brand. Note that many schools do not brand their teams in this way, so this property will not apply to all teams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Athletics Brand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a school sports team to the educational institution that the team represents.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: School

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type for collecting information about the score of a particular team within a given unit of play, e.g. first quarter, of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score by Unit of Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the score that was made by the given team in the unit of play.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the team that made the given score in the unit of play.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of play, e.g. first half, during which the given team made the score.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit of Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type containing values for the sorts of scores in a sports game, e.g. regular, extra time, and penalty.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value for matches that end in extra time, i.e. 15-minute periods that are added to the regular time for the match.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Extra Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value for matches that end with penalty shoot-outs after extra time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Penalty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value for matches that end within the 90 minutes ordinarily allotted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Regular

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains events where points are scored in a particular game, e.g. a goal is made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scoring Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the game where the scoring event took place.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the minute in the game when the score was made. Note that the expected value of this property is not datetime, because the reference is to the elapsed minutes of the game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minute

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the play that resulted in the scoring event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the player who made the score.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the value of the scoring event, e.g. a goal made or a number of points gained.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the team that was awarded the score. Note that this team may in some cases by different from the team of the player who made the score.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Score Awarded to

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the second in the game after the mso:game.scoring_event.minute when the score was made. Note that the expected value of this property is not datetime, because the reference is to the elapsed time of the game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Second

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of play, e.g. the third quarter, within which the scoring event was made.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit of Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all sports seasons. Sports seasons are the portion of the year that regulated games are in session. A year can often be broken up into several distinct sections (sometimes themselves called seasons). These are: a preseason, a series of exhibition games played for training purposes; a regular season, the main period of the league's competition; the postseason, a playoff tournament played against the league's top teams to determine the league's champion; and the offseason, the time when there is no official competition. When exactly these sections occur in the year vary by sport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports League Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a sports season to information about awards won during the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Awards

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the goalkeeper deemed the best, conceding the lowest number of goals for the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Best Goalkeeper

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the mso:sports.game during the season that has the highest points accumulated by the winning team playing in an away venue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Biggest Away Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the mso:sports.game during the season that has the highest points accumulated by the winning team playing in their home venue.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Biggest Home Win

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a sports season to an individual championship game that occurs during the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Championship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to a mso:sports.game played in the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the mso:sports.game that had the season's highest attendance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Highest Attendance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the mso:sports.game that had a team scoring the most points for the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Highest Scoring

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports season to the governing sports league.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the mso:sports.game that had the season's lowest attendance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lowest Attendance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a sports season to the number of games played in the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a sports season to the team(s) that were relegated at the conclusion of the season. Relegation occurs to the worst-ranking teams, which are moved to a lower division for the next season. Relegation (and the inverse process of promotion) generally does not happen in Canadian and American sports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Relegated Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports season to a standard descriptor for the type of season, e.g. regular or playoff.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a sports season to the statistics that are relevant to the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the mso.sports.team(s) that participated in the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports season to the athlete who was rated the number one draft pick for the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Draft Pick

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports season to the team that hired the number one draft pick for the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Draft Picker

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a sports season to the season's top scorer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Scorer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports season to the team that had the best draw for the final tournament/championship of the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Top Seed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the total number of people who attended games during the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Attendance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a sports season to the total goals scored in all of the regular season games.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Totals Goals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.season to the year the season covers. This may not be the same as the start and end dates, as the end date might include a championship that falls outside of the season year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship type collecting information on the game schedule for a given season. A game schedule is the listing of games for the season. Such lists include the date and time of the game, and the list of home and away teams.
Property relating an instance of mso:sports.season_schedule to the instance of mso:sports.season the schedule is for.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type that contains values for types of sports seasons, viz. preseason, regular season, and post season
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration for the preseason, plus the regular season, plus the postseason.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Full Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value for any games that take place after the regular season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Postseason

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value for any games that take place before the regular season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preseason

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value for any games that take place during the regular season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Regular Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that is used to specify the week within a given sports season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season Week

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the given sports season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a week within a particular sports season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Week

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A sports facility where clients can practice shooting firearms at targets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shooting Range

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A facility containing one or more areas where patrons can enjoy ice-skating or roller-skating.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Skating Rink

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling equipment for sports commonly played during winter, e.g. ice hockey, ice skating, snowshoeing, snow skiing, and snowboarding.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Snow Sports Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all sports. Sports are the types of competitive physical activity that are organized casually or professionally and aim to use, maintain, or improve physical ability and skills. Sports include football, tennis, golf, and athletics. See also mso:sports.sports_form.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:sports.sport to a mso:sports.league that governs this sport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Leagues

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating whether, in the sport, men compete against women or with women as part of the same team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mixed Gender

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:sports.sport to a mso:sports.official that officiates at games of the sport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Officials

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating whether or not the sport is played in the Olympics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Olympic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property indicating whether or not the sport is played in the Paralympics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Paralympic

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a sport to positions that players of the sport can hold.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:sports.sport to the mso:sports.equipment used in the sport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Equipment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sport to a competition, e.g. a championship, game or tournament, associated with the sport.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Establishments that specialize in selling sports equipment and accessories.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sporting Goods Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing agents that participate in sporting events, viz. sports teams and individual athletes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports agent to statistics about the team or athlete.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a sports agent to a set of statistics in which the agent is the subject or pivot of the statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a sports agent (whether a team or individual) to a multi-event tournament in which the agent has participated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournaments

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all sports clubs. Sports clubs are the organizations with the purpose of playing sports. Clubs may be dedicated to a single sport or to several (multi-sport club).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Club

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports club to a sport that is played by the club.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports club to a team that is affiliated with the club. For example, the Lakeside Lightning Basketball Club has two basketball teams, one for men and one for women.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all instances of competitive sports events, including games, tournaments, and championships.
A property that links a sports competition to a descriptor for the format of the competition, e.g. Double Round-robin and Knockout.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Format

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports competition to the governing body, e.g. the Board of Control for Cricket in India, that regulates the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports competition to a music artist who performed the national anthem at the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: National Anthem Performer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_competition to the total amount of prize money for the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Prize Money

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_competition to the mso:sports.recurring_sporting_event of which it is an event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a sports competition to the set of statistics for the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that specifies that the sports competition is a team competition, i.e. a competition in which teams rather than individual athletes participate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team Competition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_competition to the total attendance for the entire competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Attendance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sport competition to the individual, if any, who the competition. Note that this property applies only to sports competitions in which individuals rather than teams participate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winning Individual

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sport competition to the sports team, if any, that the competition. Note that this property applies only to sports competitions in which teams participate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winning Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports competition to an athlete that played on the team, if any, that won the competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Winning Team Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all sporting events. These are the events with sport as the focus of the event. Included in this type are competitions and game play, and also non-competitive events like drafts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the forms of mso:sports.sport. Forms of sports are the divisions of sports into different types. For example, the sport of tennis has forms like singles and doubles, and the sport of swimming has the forms of backstroke, butterfly, and the breaststroke.
An enumeration type containing two values to specify the side on which a player competes for a given team, viz. offense or defense.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Intention

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The side whose intention is to prevent the other side from scoring goals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Defense

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The side whose intention is to score goals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Offense

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An American Football player who is on the field during kicking plays. Note that this intention applies only to American Football, but, with respect to this sport, it is considered independent of and complementary to the standard offense/defense axis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Special Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for positions that players of a sport can hold, e.g. running back, halfback, and quarterback.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a sports position to the side, viz. offense or defense, with which the position is associated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Intention

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a sports position to information about an athlete who has held this position.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Players

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a sport in which the position is found.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data for an agent's sports statistics. These are the data about various aspects of the agent's performance in sports activities.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics to the mso:event.action_completion_category describing the completion aspect of the statistics. For example, 'attempted' versus 'made' in the context of football field goals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Action Completion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the sports agent for which the statistic is valid. Note that this property is multivalued, because in some cases the statistic has to be qualified with respect to both the athlete and the team to which the athlete belongs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the highest ranking that the given player or team has ever received by the date provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Best Ranking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of competition or match, if any, for which the statistics hold, e.g. championship.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Competition Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics relationship to the sports competition for which the statistics hold, if any.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics to the mso:sports.league in which the statistics occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the set of statistics has been adjusted (hockey) or neutralized (baseball) or altered in some other way to allow easier comparison with similar statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Normalized

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the position, if any, relative to which the athlete has the statistics provided. For example, a particular baseball player may have one set of statistics as a batter and one set of statistics as a pitcher.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistic to the ranking for the entity. This property can be used to express the ranking of the entity according to a type of statistic, like offensive rebounds in a given season, or overall ranking, like the ranking of tennis players within their league.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranking

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a ratio value, e.g. 2:3, for the given statistics. Note that this property should be used only when the ultimate value of the statistic must be stated as an unreduced numerator and denominator. Otherwise, the property mso:sports.sports_statistics.value should be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ratio Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the sports season, if any, for which the given statistic is valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics to the scope of the statistics, e.g. game, season, or career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scope

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the "narrowest" scope of a set of statistics. In other words, it specifies the scope that is to be applied before the scope indicated with the property mso:sports.sports_statistics.statistic_scope. For example, if the statistic is the number of hits per game per career, the ???game??? value would be recorded by mso:sports.sports_statistics.statistic_scope_divisor, and the "career" value would be recorded by mso:sports.sports_statistics.statistic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Statistic Scope Divisor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics relationship to the mso:sports.general_statistic_category that indicates the type of statistic the relationship covers. Note that this property is multivalued, because in some cases more than one enumeration value will apply to a particular set of statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the method of calculating the given set of statistics, e.g. average, total, and ranking. Note that the expected type of this property will eventually be changed to mso:measurement_unit.qualified_value_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Statistics Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics to the axis action category. This is the 'offense' or 'defense' axis for the statistics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strategy Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the subject or pivot of the given set of statistics. This property is necessary, because the property mso:sports.sports_statistics.agent may have, for example, a player, a team, and a league as values for the same set of statistics. The property mso:sports.sports_statistics.subject indicates unambiguously which agent the statistics are about.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a point or interval of time when the given sports statistics are or were valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time Valid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of measure, if any, that applies to the value or ratio value for the statistic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.sports_statistics relationship to the value of the given statistic for the agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all sports coaches. Coaches are the individuals that are in charge of training an athlete or team. Note the name of this term is more specific than its actual semantic content.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sports Team Coach

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating a coach to the coaching relationship the entity had with an athlete.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coach For

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:sports.sports_team_coach to the mso:sports.sports_team_coach_tenure relationship that represents the coach's current team. This is purely a derived property, and all data input should be placed on mso:sports.sports_team_coach_tenure.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
A sports team is two or more athletes working toward an objective in a competitive sport. Sports teams can be composed of professional or amateur athletes and can compete in a sport for any period of time, even for a single match or game. A coach, trainer or caddy is not considered an athlete in this context and does not count toward the "two or more" athletes required to make a team.
Things that are sports teams:
## Professional sports teams (e.g. Boston Red Sox).
## A doubles tennis pair (e.g. Serena Williams and Venus Williams).
## Commercially sponsored teams (e.g. Discovery Channel Pro Cycling Team).
## Amateur teams (e.g. AYSO Saugus, Glens Falls Greenjackets, and Pittsburgh Yellow Jackets).
## Teams assembled for a particular event (e.g. US Basketball team).
Things that are NOT sports teams:
## A company that hires people to participate in a competition individually, not as a team (e.g.: Penske racing NASCAR team). Use mso:business.operation in these cases.
## Teams not involved in athletic competition (e.g. a contract bridge team).
## A collection of sports teams or a sports association (e.g. NBA). Use mso:sports.sports_club in these cases.
## Teams not involved in competition (e.g. the Quebecers tag team in the World Wrestling Federation).

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains agents, either teams or individual players, that have competed in tournament event competitions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament event competitor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a tournament event competitor to information about the competitions in which the competitor participated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Events Competed in

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tournament event competitor to world records, if any, that are held by the competitor.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: World Record

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all groups, fixtures, or ties. These are the groupings of competitors in a tournament round. For example, 2010 FIFA World Cup Group A included the national teams from Uruguay, Mexico, South Africa, and France.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a tournament group to a round of a tournament in which the group participated
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament Round

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of individual instances of qualifying for a tournament, e.g. the 2014 FIFA World Cup qualification event and the 2008 Little League World Series qualifications. These qualifications often have several games associated with them, as teams play against each other to earn a spot in the final tournament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament Qualification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.tournament_qualification_event to the number of assured spots for the qualification event. These are the number of competitor spots open for the following competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Assured Spots

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship representing the collection of data about an agent's seeding for a given sporting event. Seeding is the preliminary ranking used in arranging a sports tournament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament Seed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.tournament_seed to the agent being seeded for the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Agent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.tournament_seed to the event for which the seeding applies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.tournament_seed to the mso:location.region that the seed represents, if any. These are usually broad geographic regions of a location, like 'south' or 'midwest'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Region

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.tournament_seed relationship to the seed value for the agent in the given tournament.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Seed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all tournament stages. These are the phases in a tournament that groups consecutive rounds. A set of stages leading to finals is a bracket.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.tournament_stage to its mso:sports.sports_tournament_rounds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Round
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: The type of this property has been deprecated. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament Team
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not needed. Use sports.team instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.team]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: tournaments_competed_in
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to sports.team. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all tournament types. These are the general groupings of tournaments with similar characteristics. Examples include 'Single-elimination tournament' and 'Round-robin tournament'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tournament Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all triathlons, which are races involving three different sports in sequence. Typically, the sports are biking, running, and swimming, but variations exist.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Triathlon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.triathlon to the distance of biking for this triathlon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Biking Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.triathlon to the distance of running for this triathlon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Running Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.triathlon to the distance of swimming for this triathlon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Swim Distance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type containing values for the various units of a sports game, e.g. first half, second quarter, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit of Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The first half of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Half

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The first fourth of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The fourth fourth of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fourth Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The second half of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Second Half

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The second fourth of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Second Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The third fourth of a sports game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Third Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An establishment where patrons can learn and/or practice the sport of volleyball, which involves hitting a ball over the net in such a way that the opposing team cannot return the ball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Volleyball Facility

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all volleyball players.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Volleyball Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.volleyball_player to the length of the player's longest block.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Block

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.volleyball_player to the length of the player's longest spike.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spike

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.volleyball_team_type to information about the members of the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting information about a player's membership on a given volleyball team, viz. the dates that the player joined and left the team and the total number of points made by the player while a member of the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Volleyball Team Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.volleyball_team_type to the date the player joined the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property specifying the total number of points scored by the player while a member of the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Points

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property specifying the given volleyball player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teammate

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:sports.volleyball_team_type to the date the player left the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A posture or position that is used in hatha yoga to strengthen or stretch a particular muscle or group of muscles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yoga Asana

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a yoga asana to another asana that is often done after the given asana.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Following Asana

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a yoga asana to another asana that is often done to prepare for the given asana or in a sequence before the given asana.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preceding Asana

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a yoga asana to the muscle or group of muscles that the asana is intended to strengthen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strengthens

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a yoga asana to the muscle or group of muscles that the asana is intended to stretch.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Stretches

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A facility where patrons can learn and/or practice yoga, a set of techniques originating in India for stretching various parts of the body to attain physical, mental, and/or spiritual fitness.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Yoga Studio
